Strong recursion principle on even and odd numbers: if for all `i : ℕ` we can prove `P (2 * i)`
from `P j` for all `j < 2 * i` and we can prove `P (2 * i + 1)` from `P j` for all `j < 2 * i + 1`,
then we have `P n` for all `n : ℕ`.

